Pamela June Crook  (born 1945), known professionally as P J Crook, is an English painter and sculptor.
Crook was born in 1945 in Cheltenham, England, where she still lives.
In 1996, Crook co-starred with musician Toyah Wilcox on the HTV short film Rolinda Sharples: Painted out of History.
Crook was appointed Member of the Order of the British Empire (MBE) in the 2011 Birthday Honours for services to art.
